In today's GREENWIRE:

TOP STORY: KLAMATH WATER CUTOFF NOT JUSTIFIED -- NAS
Government scientists did not have adequate evidence when they issued their 
biological opinions that cut off irrigation water to Klamath Basin farmers 
with the intent of protecting endangered and threatened fish last summer, 
according to a preliminary report by the National Academy of Sciences.

